<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>The Ultimate German Case Mastery Cheatsheet (A1-B2)</title>
  <!-- Tailwind CSS -->
  <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
  <!-- Google Fonts for Classical & Elegant Design -->
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@600;800&family=Lora:ital,wght=0,400;0,600;1,400&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    }
    h1, h2, h3, h4, .serif-header {
      font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    }
    .sans-ui {
      font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
    }
    @media print {
      .no-print {
        display: none !important;
      }
      body {
        background-color: #ffffff;
        color: #000000;
        font-size: 11px;
      }
      @page {
        margin: 0.3in 0.4in;
      }
      main {
        padding-top: 0 !important;
        padding-bottom: 0 !important;
      }
      .page-break {
        page-break-before: always;
        break-before: page;
        margin-top: 0 !important;
      }
      /* Tighten printing elements further to strictly lock into 2 pages */
      .print-tight-gap {
        gap: 0.75rem !important;
      }
      .print-tight-space {
        margin-top: 0.5rem !important;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem !important;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-[#faf9f6] text-stone-900 min-h-screen">

  <!-- iPad PDF Export Utility Banner -->
  <div class="no-print bg-stone-900 text-stone-100 py-2 px-6 shadow-md sans-ui text-xs">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-between gap-3">
      <p>📄 <strong>Print/PDF Setup:</strong> Tap Safari's <strong>Share</strong> → <strong>Print</strong>, pinch out on the preview to convert to a PDF, then open in <strong>GoodNotes / Notability</strong>.</p>
      <button onclick="window.print()" class="bg-white hover:bg-stone-100 text-stone-900 px-3.5 py-1 rounded-lg font-bold transition text-xs shadow-sm">
        Save / Print PDF
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- PAGE 1 CONTENT -->
  <header class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-6 pb-4 text-center border-b border-stone-200">
    <span class="sans-ui text-[9px] tracking-widest uppercase font-bold text-stone-500 block mb-1">GERMAN ELITE GRAMMAR MARATHON</span>
    <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-extrabold text-stone-800 tracking-wide">DEUTSCH GRAMMATIK</h1>
    <h2 class="text-xs md:text-sm font-medium italic text-stone-600">The Ultimate Case & Pronoun Cheatsheet</h2>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-6 space-y-6">

    <!-- COGNITIVE RULES SECTION -->
    <section class="bg-stone-100/80 border border-stone-200/80 p-4 rounded-xl space-y-3 print-tight-space">
      <h3 class="text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-700 sans-ui border-b border-stone-200 pb-1">🧠 Visual Recall Shortcuts (Mug these up first!)</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-[11px] leading-relaxed">
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <p class="font-bold text-indigo-700 uppercase tracking-wide text-[10px]">1. The Accusative is Easy</p>
          <p class="text-stone-700">Feminine (<span class="italic">die</span>), Neuter (<span class="italic">das</span>), and Plural (<span class="italic">die</span>) stay <strong>exactly identical</strong> to Nominative. Only Masculine (<span class="italic">der</span>) changes to <span class="font-semibold text-indigo-800 font-mono">den / einen / keinen</span>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <p class="font-bold text-emerald-700 uppercase tracking-wide text-[10px]">2. The Dative "M-R-M-N" Rule</p>
          <p class="text-stone-700">In the Dative, look at the definite article endings (<span class="italic">dem, der, dem, den</span>). They follow the sequence: <strong class="font-mono text-emerald-800">M - R - M - N</strong>. Masculine and Neuter are identical (<span class="italic">dem, einem</span>).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-1">
          <p class="font-bold text-amber-700 uppercase tracking-wide text-[10px]">3. The Dative Plural "Double N"</p>
          <p class="text-stone-700">In Dative plural, the article always becomes <strong class="font-mono text-amber-800">den / keinen / unseren</strong>, and the noun itself steals an extra <strong class="font-mono text-amber-800">-n</strong> at the end (e.g., <span class="italic">mit den Kindern</span>).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 1: ARTICLES -->
    <section class="space-y-3">
      <div class="border-b border-stone-200 pb-1.5 flex justify-between items-end">
        <h3 class="text-xs font-bold text-stone-800 uppercase tracking-widest">1. Master Article & Ending Table</h3>
        <span class="text-[9px] text-stone-400 font-bold uppercase sans-ui">Definite / Indefinite / Negative</span>
      </div>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto border border-stone-200 rounded-xl bg-white shadow-sm">
        <table class="w-full text-left text-[11px] text-stone-700 sans-ui border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-stone-100 text-stone-600 uppercase tracking-wider text-[9px] border-b border-stone-200">
              <th class="py-2 px-3.5 font-bold">Case</th>
              <th class="py-2 px-3.5 font-bold">Masculine <span class="text-[8px] lowercase font-normal italic text-stone-400">(der)</span></th>
              <th class="py-2 px-3.5 font-bold">Feminine <span class="text-[8px] lowercase font-normal italic text-stone-400">(die)</span></th>
              <th class="py-2 px-3.5 font-bold">Neuter <span class="text-[8px] lowercase font-normal italic text-stone-400">(das)</span></th>
              <th class="py-2 px-3.5 font-bold">Plural <span class="text-[8px] lowercase font-normal italic text-stone-400">(die)</span></th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-stone-150">
            <!-- Nominative -->
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5 font-bold text-stone-800 bg-stone-50/50">
                Nominative <span class="block text-[8px] font-normal text-stone-400 italic">(Subject)</span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5">
                <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900">der</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">ein</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">kein</span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5">
                <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900">die</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">ein<strong class="text-rose-600 font-mono">e</strong></span> / <span class="text-stone-500">kein<strong class="text-rose-600 font-mono">e</strong></span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5">
                <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900">das</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">ein</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">kein</span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5">
                <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900">die</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">—</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">kein<strong class="text-rose-600 font-mono">e</strong></span>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <!-- Accusative -->
            <tr class="bg-indigo-50/10">
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5 font-bold text-indigo-950 bg-indigo-50/20">
                Accusative <span class="block text-[8px] font-normal text-stone-400 italic">(Direct Obj.)</span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5 bg-indigo-50/30">
                <span class="text-indigo-950 font-bold underline">de<strong class="font-mono">n</strong></span> / <span class="text-indigo-700 font-bold">ein<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">en</strong></span> / <span class="text-indigo-700 font-bold">kein<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">en</strong></span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5">
                <span class="text-stone-900">die</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">eine</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">keine</span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5">
                <span class="text-stone-900">das</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">ein</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">kein</span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5">
                <span class="text-stone-900">die</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">—</span> / <span class="text-stone-500">keine</span>
              </td>
            </tr>
            <!-- Dative -->
            <tr class="bg-emerald-50/10">
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5 font-bold text-emerald-950 bg-emerald-50/20">
                Dative <span class="block text-[8px] font-normal text-stone-400 italic">(Indirect Obj.)</span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5 bg-emerald-50/20">
                <span class="text-emerald-950 font-semibold">de<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">m</strong></span> / <span class="text-emerald-700">ein<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">em</strong></span> / <span class="text-emerald-700">kein<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">em</strong></span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5 bg-emerald-50/10">
                <span class="text-emerald-950 font-semibold">de<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">r</strong></span> / <span class="text-emerald-700 font-bold">ein<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">er</strong></span> / <span class="text-emerald-700 font-bold">kein<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">er</strong></span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5 bg-emerald-50/20">
                <span class="text-emerald-950 font-semibold">de<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">m</strong></span> / <span class="text-emerald-700">ein<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">em</strong></span> / <span class="text-emerald-700">kein<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">em</strong></span>
              </td>
              <td class="py-2 px-3.5 bg-emerald-50/30">
                <span class="text-emerald-950 font-bold">de<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">n</strong></span> / <span class="text-stone-400">—</span> / <span class="text-emerald-700 font-bold">kein<strong class="font-mono text-rose-600">en (+n)</strong></span>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DUAL COLUMNS: PERSONAL PRONOUNS & POSSESSIVE BASE WORDS -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-start print-tight-gap">
      
      <!-- LEFT SIDE: PERSONAL PRONOUNS (7 COLS) -->
      <section class="space-y-3 md:col-span-7">
        <div class="border-b border-stone-200 pb-1.5 flex justify-between items-end">
          <h3 class="text-xs font-bold text-stone-800 uppercase tracking-widest">2. Personal Pronouns</h3>
          <span class="text-[9px] text-stone-400 font-bold uppercase sans-ui">Replacing People</span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="overflow-x-auto border border-stone-200 rounded-xl bg-white shadow-sm">
          <table class="w-full text-left text-[11px] text-stone-700 sans-ui border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-stone-100 text-stone-600 uppercase tracking-wider text-[9px] border-b border-stone-200">
                <th class="py-2 px-3 font-bold">Nom.</th>
                <th class="py-2 px-3 font-bold text-indigo-700">Akk.</th>
                <th class="py-2 px-3 font-bold text-emerald-700">Dat.</th>
                <th class="py-2 px-3 font-bold">Trigger Clue</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-stone-150">
              <tr>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 font-bold">ich</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-indigo-600 font-semibold">mich</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-emerald-600 font-semibold">mir</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-stone-500 italic text-[10px]">helfen &rarr; mir</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 font-bold">du</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-indigo-600 font-semibold">dich</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-emerald-600 font-semibold">dir</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-stone-500 italic text-[10px]">Wie geht's dir?</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-stone-50/40">
                <td class="py-1 px-3 font-bold">er / es</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-indigo-950 font-bold">ihn / es</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-emerald-950 font-bold">ihm</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-stone-500 italic text-[10px]">Ich suche ihn.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-stone-50/40">
                <td class="py-1 px-3 font-bold">sie</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-indigo-600 font-semibold">sie</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-emerald-600 font-semibold">ihr</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-stone-500 italic text-[10px]">Es gehört ihr.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 font-bold">wir</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-indigo-700 font-bold">uns</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-emerald-700 font-bold">uns</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-stone-500 italic text-[10px]">mit uns (Dative)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 font-bold">ihr</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-indigo-600 font-semibold">euch</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-emerald-600 font-semibold">euch</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-stone-500 italic text-[10px]">Ich rufe euch an.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-stone-50/40">
                <td class="py-1 px-3 font-bold">sie / Sie</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-indigo-600 font-semibold">sie / Sie</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-emerald-950 font-bold">ihnen / Ihnen</td>
                <td class="py-1 px-3 text-stone-500 italic text-[10px]">Wie geht es Ihnen?</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- RIGHT SIDE: POSSESSIVE BASE WORDS (5 COLS) -->
      <section class="space-y-3 md:col-span-5">
        <div class="border-b border-stone-200 pb-1.5 flex justify-between items-end">
          <h3 class="text-xs font-bold text-stone-800 uppercase tracking-widest">3. Possessives</h3>
          <span class="text-[9px] text-stone-400 font-bold uppercase sans-ui">Owner Base</span>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2 text-[11px] sans-ui">
          <div class="bg-white p-2.5 border border-stone-200 rounded-lg">
            <span class="text-[8px] font-bold uppercase text-stone-400 block leading-none">I (My)</span>
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">mein-</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-2.5 border border-stone-200 rounded-lg">
            <span class="text-[8px] font-bold uppercase text-stone-400 block leading-none">You (Your)</span>
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">dein-</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-2.5 border border-stone-200 rounded-lg">
            <span class="text-[8px] font-bold uppercase text-stone-400 block leading-none">He/It (His)</span>
            <p class="font-bold text-indigo-700">sein-</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-2.5 border border-stone-200 rounded-lg">
            <span class="text-[8px] font-bold uppercase text-stone-400 block leading-none">She (Her)</span>
            <p class="font-bold text-amber-700">ihr-</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-2.5 border border-stone-200 rounded-lg">
            <span class="text-[8px] font-bold uppercase text-stone-400 block leading-none">We (Our)</span>
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">unser-</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-2.5 border border-stone-200 rounded-lg">
            <span class="text-[8px] font-bold uppercase text-stone-400 block leading-none">You all (Your)</span>
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">euer- <span class="text-[8px] font-normal text-stone-400">(eure)</span></p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-2.5 border border-stone-200 rounded-lg col-span-2 bg-indigo-50/25 border-indigo-200">
            <span class="text-[8px] font-bold uppercase text-indigo-500 block leading-none">You formal / They</span>
            <p class="font-bold text-indigo-900">Ihr- <span class="text-[8px] font-normal text-indigo-400">(Formal Capitalized!)</span> / ihr-</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- FORCE PAGE BREAK FOR PERFECT 2-PAGE LAYOUT -->
    <div class="page-break"></div>

    <!-- PAGE 2 CONTENT -->
    <section class="space-y-4 pt-4">
      <div class="border-b border-stone-300 pb-2 flex justify-between items-end">
        <h3 class="text-xs font-bold text-stone-800 uppercase tracking-widest">4. Case Triggers</h3>
        <span class="text-[9px] text-stone-400 font-bold uppercase sans-ui">Verbs & Prepositions</span>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-[11px] leading-relaxed">
        
        <!-- ACCUSATIVE TRIGGERS -->
        <div class="border border-indigo-100 bg-indigo-50/10 p-4 rounded-xl space-y-3">
          <h4 class="font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-indigo-800 border-b border-indigo-100 pb-1 sans-ui text-xs">🎯 Accusative Triggers</h4>
          
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="font-semibold text-indigo-900">1. Major Action Verbs (Ownership & Consumption)</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-2 gap-y-0.5 text-stone-600 font-mono text-[10px]">
              <div>haben <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to have)</span></div>
              <div>kaufen <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to buy)</span></div>
              <div>essen <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to eat)</span></div>
              <div>trinken <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to drink)</span></div>
              <div>suchen <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to search)</span></div>
              <div>sehen <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to see)</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="font-semibold text-indigo-900">2. Accusative-Only Prepositions</p>
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-900 font-mono bg-white px-2 py-1 rounded border border-indigo-150 inline-block text-[10px] shadow-sm">
              für <span class="text-stone-400 font-sans font-normal text-[9px]">(for)</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; 
              ohne <span class="text-stone-400 font-sans font-normal text-[9px]">(without)</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; 
              durch <span class="text-stone-400 font-sans font-normal text-[9px]">(through)</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; 
              gegen <span class="text-stone-400 font-sans font-normal text-[9px]">(against)</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- DATIVE TRIGGERS -->
        <div class="border border-emerald-100 bg-emerald-50/10 p-4 rounded-xl space-y-3">
          <h4 class="font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-emerald-800 border-b border-emerald-100 pb-1 sans-ui text-xs">🍀 Dative Triggers</h4>
          
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">1. Dative Verbs (Giving & Helping)</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-2 gap-y-0.5 text-stone-600 font-mono text-[10px]">
              <div>helfen <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to help)</span></div>
              <div>danken <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to thank)</span></div>
              <div>gehören <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to belong to)</span></div>
              <div>gefallen <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to please)</span></div>
              <div>passen <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to fit)</span></div>
              <div>schmecken <span class="text-[8px] text-stone-400 font-sans">(to taste)</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">2. Dative-Only Prepositions</p>
            <p class="font-bold text-stone-900 font-mono bg-white px-2 py-1 rounded border border-emerald-150 inline-block text-[10px] shadow-sm leading-normal">
              mit <span class="text-stone-400 font-sans font-normal text-[9px]">(with)</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; 
              zu <span class="text-stone-400 font-sans font-normal text-[9px]">(to)</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; 
              bei <span class="text-stone-400 font-sans font-normal text-[9px]">(at/with)</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; 
              nach <span class="text-stone-400 font-sans font-normal text-[9px]">(after)</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; 
              aus <span class="text-stone-400 font-sans font-normal text-[9px]">(from)</span>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- THE WECHSELPREPOSITION DUAL NATURE -->
      <div class="border border-stone-200 bg-white p-4 rounded-xl space-y-3">
        <h4 class="font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-800 border-b border-stone-200 pb-1 sans-ui text-center text-xs">🔄 Two-Way Prepositions (Wechselpräpositionen)</h4>
        <p class="text-[11px] text-stone-600 italic text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Prepositions like <strong class="font-mono">in, auf, an, unter, über, neben, hinter, vor, zwischen</strong> change case depending on movement and bounds.
        </p>

        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-[11px] leading-relaxed">
          <div class="bg-indigo-50/20 border border-indigo-100/50 p-3.5 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-bold text-indigo-900 uppercase tracking-wide text-[9px] mb-0.5">Direction / Destination (Accusative)</p>
            <p class="font-bold text-slate-800 text-xs">Wohin? <span class="font-normal text-stone-500 font-sans italic text-[10px]">(Where to?)</span></p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 text-[10.5px]">Crossing a border, going from point A into point B.</p>
            <div class="bg-white p-2 rounded border border-indigo-100 font-mono text-stone-700 text-[10px] mt-1.5 italic">
              Ich gehe <span class="text-indigo-600 font-bold">in den</span> Park. <span class="text-stone-400 not-italic font-sans text-[9px]">(der Park &rarr; den)</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-emerald-50/20 border border-emerald-100/50 p-3.5 rounded-lg">
